    ğŸ”¹ `--dry-run` --> ğŸ§ª Do not actually remove the sockets, just print out which ones would be removed.
    ğŸ”¹ `--age=SECONDS` --> â³ Only remove sockets older than `SECONDS` seconds.  If not specified, the default is `3600` (one hour).
    ğŸ”¹ `--systemd-activation` --> âš™ï¸ Assume systemd activation is used (regardless of whether systemd is actually being used).

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ dbus-cleanup-sockets

    ğŸ”¹ Removes DBus sockets that have not been used in over an hour.

    $ dbus-cleanup-sockets --verbose

    ğŸ”¹ Removes DBus sockets that have not been used in over an hour and prints information about the sockets being removed.

    $ sudo dbus-cleanup-sockets --age=300

    ğŸ”¹ Removes DBus sockets that have not been used in over 5 minutes (300 seconds), requiring root privileges.

